---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Kitchen Renovations Dickson | Inner-North Character Homes"
  description="Kitchen renovations in Dickson and Canberra's inner-north — heritage-sympathetic and high-end kitchens for period and mid-century homes, with custom cabinetry and stone benchtops. ACT-licensed. Free quote."
  canonical="https://kitchenrenovationscanberra.com.au/dickson/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Dickson &middot; Ainslie &middot; Hackett &middot; Watson &middot; Lyneham</span>
      <h1>Kitchen renovations in <span class="accent">Dickson</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Dickson and Canberra&rsquo;s inner-north are full of character &mdash;
        period and mid-century homes in established, sought-after streets. We do
        the kind of kitchen work these homes deserve: heritage-sympathetic,
        high-end, with custom cabinetry and quality stone that respects the
        house.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Dickson</span>
      <h2>The Dickson kitchen story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Inner-north character &mdash; period and mid-century homes.</h3>
        <p>
          Dickson sits in Canberra&rsquo;s established inner-north, surrounded by
          Ainslie, Hackett, Watson, Lyneham and Downer &mdash; suburbs known for
          their early-Canberra cottages, mid-century homes and leafy,
          high-demand streets. The kitchens in these homes are often original or
          poorly renovated decades ago, and owners here want work that&rsquo;s
          <strong>sympathetic to the character of the house</strong> while
          functioning as a thoroughly modern kitchen.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Heritage-sympathetic, high-end work.</h3>
        <p>
          The inner-north brief is rarely a budget rip-and-replace &mdash;
          it&rsquo;s a considered, high-end renovation that fits the home.
          That can mean Shaker-style or timber cabinetry, a natural stone
          benchtop, and details that suit a period or mid-century aesthetic,
          all built to modern standards underneath. Our
          <a href="/services/custom-cabinetry/">custom cabinetry</a> is ideal
          here because character homes almost never have standard openings, and
          our <a href="/services/kitchen-design/">design</a> process makes sure
          the new kitchen sits naturally in the home.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Character homes need careful handling.</h3>
        <p>
          Older inner-north homes can have non-standard construction, sub-floor
          services to re-route, and bonded asbestos in mid-century wall sheeting,
          floor backing and old splashbacks &mdash; and the ACT carries the Mr
          Fluffy loose-fill asbestos legacy (1968&ndash;1980). We identify and
          arrange licensed removal of suspect materials before demolition, and
          where a renovation alters structure or the building envelope we advise
          on <strong>ACTPLA approval</strong> and any heritage or planning
          considerations. We get the paperwork right rather than risk a
          character home.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Modern standards under a classic finish.</h3>
        <p>
          A character kitchen still has to perform. We deliver compliant
          plumbing to <strong>AS/NZS 3500</strong>, electrical to <strong>AS/NZS
          3000</strong>, and wet-area waterproofing to <strong>AS 3740</strong>
          where it adjoins, all by ACT-licensed trades under the
          <strong>Construction Occupations (Licensing) Act 2004</strong>. Compliant
          stone only after the 2024 engineered-stone ban. The result looks like
          it belongs in the house and works like a brand-new kitchen.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Dickson kitchen jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Heritage-sympathetic kitchen in an early-Canberra Ainslie cottage ($40K&ndash;$75K)</li>
          <li>Mid-century home kitchen with timber custom cabinetry and natural stone in Hackett</li>
          <li>High-end full renovation opening a Lyneham kitchen to living areas</li>
          <li>Pre-demolition asbestos clearance and re-cabinet on a period Watson home</li>
          <li>Shaker-style cabinetry and a marble or quartzite benchtop in Downer</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/belconnen/">Belconnen</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/gungahlin/">Gungahlin</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/tuggeranong/">Tuggeranong</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/woden/">Woden</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/canberra-region/">All Canberra &amp; the ACT</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Dickson kitchen quote.</h2>
        <p>Heritage-sympathetic, high-end inner-north kitchens. Custom cabinetry, quality stone, fixed-price quotes.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
